  "stimulus_html": "Halogenated compounds are particularly easy to identify by their mass spectra because both chlorine and bromine occur naturally as mixtures of two abundant isotopes. Recall that chlorine occurs as <sup>35</sup>Cl (75.8%) and <sup>37</sup>Cl (24.2%); and bromine occurs as <sup>79</sup>Br (50.7%) and <sup>81</sup>Br (49.3%). At what masses do the molecular ions occur for the following formulas? What are the relative percentages of each molecular ion?",
